title: 2.6.2.1 - Precipitation Extremes
section 2_6_2_1

  |Further analyses continue to support the {cite.1.'IPCC_2007 AR4} and SREX conclusions that it is likely that there have been statistically significant increases in the number of heavy precipitation events in more regions than there have been statistically significant decreases, but there are strong regional and subregional variations in the trends.


  

